    "impact": "Increases development cycles, introduces bugs into consuming applications, and degrades the overall quality of the integrated system.",
    "priority": "High"
  },
  {
    "finding": "The security of the JWT authentication mechanism is a foundational requirement and must be implemented following best practices.",
    "evidence": "Improper JWT handling (e.g., weak secrets, insecure storage, lack of expiration/refresh) can lead to severe security vulnerabilities like unauthorized access or data breaches.",
    "impact": "Compromised user data, loss of user trust, legal and reputational damage for the applications built on top of this API.",
    "priority": "Critical"
  },
  {
    "finding": "API performance directly translates to end-user satisfaction in the applications consuming it.",
    "evidence": "Slow API responses cause laggy frontend experiences, leading to user frustration and potential abandonment of the application.",
    "impact": "Negative user experience, reduced engagement, and potential loss of users for the applications built using this API.",
    "priority": "Medium"
  },
  {
    "finding": "Clear and comprehensive documentation is the primary interface for developers interacting with a backend-only API.",
    "evidence": "Without direct UI, developers rely solely on documentation to understand how to use the API, its capabilities, and its constraints.",
    "impact": "Lack of good documentation leads to misinterpretations, incorrect implementations, and a steep learning curve for integrators.",
    "priority": "High"
  }
],
[
  {
    "improvement": "Implement OpenAPI/Swagger for interactive API documentation.",
    "details": "Automatically generate and host a Swagger UI that provides detailed descriptions of all endpoints, request/response schemas, authentication methods, and example payloads. This will significantly improve the developer experience for 'Alex, The Frontend Developer'."
